Package structs

Class PumpGeneralStruct

  • java.lang.Object
    • structs.PumpGeneralStruct
  • public class PumpGeneralStruct
extends java.lang.Object
    The PumpGeneralStruct class represents the general properties of pumps in a network optimization scenario.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field Description
      double capitalcost_per_kw
      The capital cost per kilowatt of a pump in Rupees per kilowatt.
      int design_lifetime
      The number of years for which the energy cost is to be considered.
      double discount_rate
      The rate by which future energy cost is discounted to compute the present value of the cost, expressed as a percentage.
      double efficiency
      The efficiency of the pump expressed as a percentage.
      double energycost_factor
      The factor by which the energy cost of the pump is multiplied.
      double energycost_per_kwh
      The energy cost per kilowatt-hour of a pump in Rupees per kilowatt-hour.
      double inflation_rate
      The rate by which future energy cost is increased, expressed as a percentage.
      double minpumpsize
      minimum pump power allowed in kW
      int[] must_not_pump
      The list of pipes (represented by their pipe IDs) that cannot have pumps installed.
      boolean pump_enabled
      true if pumps are to be optimized
